<keyStep pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,159,411]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<keyLead pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
7. Thallus thicker (more than 2 layers), not translucent; antheridia borne on special branches; sporophyte in a dark, swollen, mussellike bivalved involucre below the thallus apex foot and seta of sporophyte well developed ...................................... 
<taxonomicName box="[1308,1451,332,354]" class="Marchantiopsida" family="Targioniaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Marchantiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="family">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1308,1451,332,354]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Targioniaceae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
